XIV.

This is taken from the long Reliqious symposium of Erasmus. It contains one of his most striking sayings :—‘ Perhaps the spirit of Christ is poured more widely than is admitted in our interpretation.' This is illustrated by a quotation from Cato's famous speech in Cicero’s de senectute and by reference to statements of Socrates as given by Plato. The words Sancte Socrates, ora pro nobis have almost passed into a proverb. ‘ Socrates a Christian Saint’ has been the theme of not a few writers, ancient and modern.
